                <h4>List A:</h4>

    
              <p>9 credits from:</p>
    
              <ul class="program-set">
                  <li class="program-course">
            <a href="/study/2014-2015/courses/agec-333" class="program-course-title">
              AGEC 333 Resource Economics (3 credits)              <!---->            </a>
            <div class="program-course-description">
              <div class="program-course-description-inner">
                <div id="node-17410" class=" clearfix">
  
  
  
  <div class="meta">
    <p>Offered by: Agricultural Economics (<a href="/study/2014-2015/node/606">Agricultural &amp; Environmental Sciences</a>)</p>
      </div>

  <div class="content">
    <h3>Overview</h3>

    <p>
      Agricultural Economics              : The role of resources in the environment, use of resources, and management of economic resources within the firm or organization. Problem-solving, case studies involving private and public decision-making in organizations are utilized.          </p>

    <p class="catalog-terms">
      Terms:              Fall 2014          </p>

