                  <li class="program-course">
            <a href="/study/2014-2015/courses/econ-326" class="program-course-title">
              ECON 326 Ecological Economics (3 credits)              <!---->            </a>
            <div class="program-course-description">
              <div class="program-course-description-inner">
                <div id="node-22368" class=" clearfix">
  
  
  
  <div class="meta">
    <p>Offered by: Economics (<a href="/study/2014-2015/node/607">Faculty of Arts</a>)</p>
      </div>

  <div class="content">
    <h3>Overview</h3>

    <p>
      Economics (Arts)              : Macroeconomic and structural aspects of the ecological crisis. A course in which subjects discussed include the conflict between economic growth and the laws of thermodynamics; the search for alternative economic indicators; the fossil fuels crisis; and "green'' fiscal policy.          </p>

    <p class="catalog-terms">
      Terms:              Fall 2014, Winter 2015          </p>

